[1]
Date: 13 Jun 2002
From: Pablo Nart <p.nart@virgin.net>
Source Xinhua News Agency, Tue 11 June 2002 [edited]

Cambodia: Dengue Fever and Malaria Cases on the Increase
--------------------------------------------------------
Malaria and dengue fever have been prevalent recently in some provinces and
municipalities in Cambodia, said Duong Socheat, Director of the National
Center for Parasitology, Entomology and Malaria Control. He said and the
World Health Organization (WHO) is helping Cambodia eliminate mosquitos
related to the diseases.
The morbidity of malaria and dengue rose steeply in Phnom Penh, and the
Provinces of Kandal, Kompong Cham, and Banteay Meanchey, where a total of
1007 people were found to have contracted the 2 diseases, he said, adding
some of them have been hospitalized and 3 people have died. Malaria and
Dengue have now spread to other provinces such as Takeo and Kampot, and
even Stung Treng Province, where dengue has not been seen during the past 6
years.
The WHO office in Phnom Penh has donated 80 tons of mosquito pesticides to
the affected areas, and it will provide another 40 tons to help kill the pests
--
