[3]
Date: Thu 13 Jun 2002
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Agencia EFE (via COMTEX), Wed 12 Jun 2002 [edited]

Guatemala: "Yellow Alert" Declared Due to Dengue in El Salvador
---------------------------------------------------------------
GUATEMALA CITY: Guatemalan health officials declared a permanent "yellow
alert" along the Salvadoran border due to an epidemic of dengue fever in
that country, a government spokesman said on Wed 12 Jun 2002.
Guatemalan Public Health and Social Assistance Ministry spokesman Jose
Candido Barrillas said that a health cordon has been strengthened in the
border region. Barrillas told EFE that the "yellow alert" along the
Guatemalan-Salvadoran border will be permanent due to the constant flow of
Salvadorans into Guatemala.
Only one case of dengue hemorrhagic fever was reported in Guatemala last
year, and so far this year, there have been no cases reported. However,
there have been 818 suspected cases of classic dengue of which 33 have been
confirmed.
