[4]
Date: Sun 16 Jun 2002
From: Pablo Nart <p.nart@virgin.net>
Source: Agence France Press, Fri 14 Jun 2002 [edited]

El Salvador: State of Emergency Declared in 4 Provinces
----------------------------------------------------------
President Francisco Flores has declared a state of emergency in 4 of El
Salvador's 14 provinces due to a dengue fever outbreak that has caused 4
deaths among 1042 reported cases. "We are declaring a state of emergency in
San Salvador, La Libertad, Santa Ana and Cabanas Departments," Flores said
late on Thu 13 Jun 2002. The state of emergency places the Defense Ministry
in charge of efforts to combat the spread of the epidemic, and frees up
state funds to help affected populations.
Health authorities said that between January and the first week of June
2002, 1042 Salvadorans have contracted dengue fever, 90 of them developing
the more dangerous form -- dengue hemorrhagic fever. So far 4 people have died.
Carried by the _Aedes aegypti_ mosquito, dengue fever causes intense
headaches, vomiting, and muscle and joint pains. In fatal cases, victims
often do not recognize that they are infected and fail to seek proper
treatment. They quickly lose blood plasma and go into shock after the
initial fever passes.
