[5]
Date: Mon 17 Jun 2002
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Xinhua News Agency (via COMTEX), Sun 16 Jun 2002 [edited]

Sri Lanka: More Dengue Fever Cases Reported
-------------------------------------------
COLOMBO: Dengue fever has spread in Sri Lanka with over 2000 confirmed
cases identified in May 2002 and 15 deaths reported, according to the
Health Ministry on Mon 17 Jun 2002. A further 3400 suspected cases of
dengue fever have been reported from different parts of the country since
the beginning of this year with 35 cases in Colombo city.
The epidemic reached its height in 2000 when over 6000 suspected cases were
hospitalized throughout the country and 35 lives were lost. The highest
number of Dengue cases this year have been reported from the Gampaha
district near the capital Colombo.
The Epidemiological unit has called for immediate steps to prevent the
killer disease spreading. An awareness program has been launched regarding
the fever itself and preventive measures are to be adopted. The change in
weather patterns and heavy rains after a long spell of drought is
considered one of the causes for the spread of the fever enabling the
mosquitos to breed freely.
--
